gomodel:SYNGO_3049  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Electron microscopy localization of dicer and eIF2c in dendritic spines in cortex and hippocampal area CA1\"\n- \"Electron microscopy immunocytochemistry using peroxidase-based detection confirmed that dicer-like immunoreactivity was present within dendritic spines and appeared to be particularly associated with PSDs (Figs3a and c). eIF2c was also prominent in spines (Fig. 3b).\"\n\nFig.6: \"Expression of dicer and eIF2c in brain subcellular fractions\"\n- \":A dicer-immunoreactive band was also enriched in PSDs that was approximately twice the size of native dicer, but which was not affected by boiling and reduction of the sample (Fig. 6); it is not clear whether this represents dimeric dicer or a sodium dodecyl sulfate-resistant complex of dicer with another protein(s). \"\n\n28/3/2018 Pim\n- Antibody for Argonaut is not gene specific: \"a peptide corresponding to the C-terminal 16 amino acids of eIF2c1 was used as antigen in rabbits (the C-terminal 16 amino acids are identical in eIF2c2; there is one mismatch in eIF2c3 and four mismatches in eIF2c4).\" Annotation for this protein was not made.. Experimental description: - All experiments were performed in mice" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3049" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

